Little Red Riding Hood is a fairy tale about a young girl who is given a red cloak by her mother and told to visit her sick grandmother.
On her way to her grandmother's house, Little Red Riding Hood encounters a wolf who asks her where she is going.
The girl tells the wolf that she is going to visit her grandmother, and the wolf suggests that he take a shortcut and get there before her.

When Little Red Riding Hood arrives at her grandmother's house, she finds that the wolf has already gotten there and eaten her grandmother.
The wolf then tries to eat Little Red Riding Hood as well, but she is rescued by a huntsman who cuts her and her grandmother out of the wolf's belly.

The story of Little Red Riding Hood is a cautionary tale about the dangers of talking to strangers and straying from the path.
